# Alembic Migrations

Generic single-database configuration for the AI Gateway backend.

Run all commands from `backend/`:

```bash
cd backend
uv run python -m alembic upgrade head
```

## Prerequisites

1. PostgreSQL running (`docker compose up -d` from project root)
2. `.env` at project root with `DATABASE_URL` matching Docker credentials (copy from `.env.example`)

## Common commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `uv run python -m alembic upgrade head` | Apply all migrations |
| `uv run python -m alembic downgrade -1` | Roll back one revision |
| `uv run python -m alembic downgrade base` | Drop all application tables |
| `uv run python -m alembic current` | Show applied revision |
| `uv run python -m alembic history` | List revision chain |
| `uv run python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"` | Generate migration from model changes |
| `uv run python -m alembic upgrade head --sql` | Preview SQL without applying |

## Notes

- Uses async `postgresql+asyncpg` via `alembic/env.py`
- Metadata source: `src.models.Base` (all models imported via `src.models`)
- Initial migration: `a3f6c2d18e01` — creates 7 domain tables
